The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for controlling the motion of an artificial agent in a group coordination task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The coordination task involves synchronizing with a human group, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
